dataset.title: Clinics and Hospitals
dataset.description: A point data-set that represents the locations of clinics and hospitals throughout Waupaca County.

dataset.title: Driveways
dataset.description: A line data-set that represents a comprehensive, spatially referenced collection of driveway locations that service the addressed locations as recognized by the Waupaca County Land Information Office.

dataset.title: Addresses
dataset.description: A point data-set that represents a comprehensive, spatially referenced collection of site addresses as recognized by Waupaca County.  This layer represents the location/address of primary structures (generally residential housing) throughout the County.

dataset.title: Road Right-of-Way (ROW)
dataset.description: The road right-of-way(ROW) layer for Waupaca County includes county, state, and U.S. highways, town roads, city streets and alleys. The Road ROW layer is available in a county-wide or individual layer for each township, city, or village. The road ROW polygons were derived from various sources. These sources include, but are not limited to, deeds, surveys, subdivision plats, highway plats, Town records, and State records.

dataset.title: Tax Parcels
dataset.description: Tax parcel map of Waupaca County, Wisconsin. The layer was derived from a variety of source maps including: mylar county parcel maps, plats of surveys, deed descriptions, subdivision maps, certified survey maps, highway right-of-way plats, and township highway right-of-way maps. These source materials were of several different scales and were from dates ranging from the early 1850's to the present. This map provides a useful representation of the geometry and topology of tax parcels and is suitable for its intended purpose. It is not, however, meant to be used for the determination of land ownership or to be in any way a substitute for the land ownership and interest descriptions contained in individual deeds.  The tax parcel layer is available in a county-wide or individual layer for each township, city, or village.

dataset.title: Tax Roll - Real Estate
dataset.description:
Data table Code Definitions
A copy of the full real estate tax file.  This table includes a detailed property assessment break down for every property within Waupaca County, WI.  The data is intended to be joined to the Tax Parcel Polygons using the "PIN" field.

dataset.title: Conservation Easements
dataset.description: Dataset represents various permanent conservation easements throughout the county.  These easements include perpetual NRCS Conservation Reserve Easement Program (CREP) areas, Waupaca County donated conservation easements and private Land Trust easements.

dataset.title: Aerial Imagery - 2015 (North West)
dataset.description:
2.5 GB FILE, a single seamless MrSID image (Generation 3).  Digital orthophotos combine the geometric qualities of a map with the image 
qualities of a photograph. The imagery collected during this flight has a ground 
resolution of 0.5 US foot x 0.5 US Foot.  This is 4-band imagery, which means bands 1-3 are RGB and band 4 is Near Infrared.

dataset.title: Aerial Imagery - 2000
dataset.description: 252 MB ZIP FILE, contains a single seamless MrSID image.  Digital orthophotos combine the geometric qualities of a map with the image qualities of a photograph. The imagery collected during this flight has a ground resolution of 1 US foot x 1 US Foot.  The image is a mosaic of the entire county.

dataset.title: Aerial Imagery - 1994
dataset.description:
194 MB ZIP FILE, contains a single seamless MrSID image.  Digital orthophotos combine the geometric qualities of a map with the image 
qualities of a photograph. The imagery collected during this flight has a ground 
resolution of 2 US foot x 2 US Foot at a scale of 1:1700. The 
image is a mosaic of the entire county and has a geographic extent of 202,239 x 
161,121 feet, with a 300-foot buffer around the County and is available in MrSID 
format. Individual township MrSID images are also available.

dataset.title: Real Estate Comparative Sales
dataset.description: Real estate sales history data.  This includes parcel numbers, owner names, property type, sale date and sale amount.

dataset.title: Tax Roll - Tax History
dataset.description:
Two previous years of real estate taxes and payment history.  This table includes a detailed break down of tax amounts and payments for every property within Waupaca County, WI. 
 The data is intended to be joined to the Tax Parcel Polygons using the 
"TXPRCL" field.

dataset.title: Public Land Survey System (PLSS) GPS Control
dataset.description: Public Land Survey System (PLSS) monuments that have established survey grade GPS coordinates.

dataset.title: Municipal Boundaries
dataset.description: A polygon data-set that represents the jurisdictional boundaries for cities, towns and villages throughout Waupaca County, Wisconsin.

dataset.title: Other Survey Control
dataset.description: Various survey ground control monuments (NGS, WIDOT, County Highway Benchmarks) with established Waupaca County coordinates.

dataset.title: School Districts
dataset.description: A polygon data-set that represents the jurisdictional boundaries of public school districts throughout Waupaca County, Wisconsin.

dataset.title: Aquatic Invasives
dataset.description: Point locations where aquatic invasive plant species have been identified.

dataset.title: Public Land Survey System (PLSS) Index
dataset.description: Public Land Survey System Network for Waupaca County, WI.  The layer was derived from a variety of source maps including PLSS corner tie sheets, section summaries and other survey maps filed in the County Surveyor's office.  Quarter and Quarter-Quarter divisions were established by existing survey when applicable.  In the absence of survey data straight line intersects between quarter corners was used to establish quarter and quarter-quarter lines.  The index layer is available in a county-wide or individual layer for each township, city, or village.

dataset.title: Park Areas
dataset.description: A polygon data-set that represents the location of all park boundaries within Waupaca County, Wisconsin.  This includes State Parks, County Parks, Town Parks, and City/Village Parks.

dataset.title: Voting Wards
dataset.description: A polygon data-set that represents voting district boundaries throughout Waupaca County, Wisconsin.  These boundaries were adopted during the 2010 redistricting process.

dataset.title: Schools (Public)
dataset.description: A point data-set that represents the locations of public school facilities throughout Waupaca County.

dataset.title: Zoning
dataset.description: Rural zoning districts for townships that fall under Waupaca County Zoning. Zoning data is tax parcel based.

dataset.title: Trails
dataset.description:
A poly line data-set that represents all known locations of trails 
within Waupaca County, Wisconsin.  This includes State Trails, County Trails, and City/Village Trails.

dataset.title: Aquatic Invasive Areas
dataset.description: Polygon area locations where aquatic invasive plant species have been identified.

dataset.title: County Supervisor Districts
dataset.description: A polygon data-set that represents the jurisdictional boundaries for the county supervisory districts throughout Waupaca County, Wisconsin.  These boundaries were adopted during the 2010 redistricting process.

dataset.title: LiDAR - Bare Earth - GeoTiff
dataset.description: 2.23 GB ZIP FILE, contains a single seamless raster in GeoTIFF format.

dataset.title: Water Areas
dataset.description: The hydrography coverage was created to represent rivers, water bodies and other hydrographic phenomena in Waupaca County. Hydrologic features were derived from the May 1994 flight with a flight height of 10,000 feet.

dataset.title: Water Lines
dataset.description: The hydrography coverage was created to represent rivers, water bodies and other hydrographic phenomena in Waupaca County. Hydrologic features were derived from the May 1994 flight with a flight height of 10,000 feet

dataset.title: Schools (Private)
dataset.description: A point data-set that represents the locations of private school facilities throughout Waupaca County.

dataset.title: Specialized Health Care Facilities
dataset.description: A point data-set that represents the locations of specialized health care facilities throughout Waupaca County.

dataset.title: Download LiDAR Tiles (.dwg & .las)
dataset.description: There is no description available.

dataset.title: Snowmobile Trails
dataset.description: A poly line data-set that represents all known locations of snowmobile trails within Waupaca County, Wisconsin.  Due to the nature of snowmobile trails, some segments may change from year-to-year.  This data may not be current for winter 2016.

dataset.title: Roads and Streets
dataset.description: A line data-set that represents the Waupaca County transportation network. A single line is used to represent the center of a road. All roads are geocoded with a address range.

dataset.title: Park Locations
dataset.description: A point data-set that represents discrete location of all parks within Waupaca County, Wisconsin.  This includes State Parks, County Parks, Town Parks, and City/Village Parks.

dataset.title: Preferred Land Use
dataset.description: Comprehensive planning preferred land use.  Data was generated through a grassroots effort facilitated by township level planning commission meetings.  Township planning commissions identified how they wanted to see the land used in the future, 2030 be the target date.

dataset.title: LiDAR - Bare Earth - GRID
dataset.description: 2.1 GB ZIP FILE, contains a single seamless raster in GRID format.

dataset.title: Existing Land Use
dataset.description: A polygon data-set for the County of Waupaca's land use plus all of New London and Marion.  It was an updated in 2010 using county aerial imagery.

dataset.title: LiDAR - Point Cloud - GRID
dataset.description: 1.8 GB ZIP FILE, contains a single seamless raster in GRID format.

dataset.title: Contours - South Western Quadrant (.shp)
dataset.description:
1.8 GB ZIP FILE Contains Shapefiles: LiDAR data collection and quality control has been conducted in accordance wih 
the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) guidelines and specifications for 
gathering data necessary to create digital elevation models using the guidelines 
and specifications in place at the beginning of the task order. The survey 
includes select areas and over and within Waupaca County. Waupaca County LiDAR 
Survey was performed using government furnished maps outlining specific areas 
for the purpose of gathering data necessary to create digital elevation models 
in accordance with the guidelines and specifications directed by owner, and 
contract Scope of Work. The raw LiDAR data density (posting) will be 
approximately 3-meters. The total area of the survey is 70,339.72 acres.  Elevation values are referenced to NADV88.
